i’m in the part you talk about your health and i want to share this. when i was 12 i found out i had leukemia, at that time i didn’t even know what it was... then i started to feel bad, like really really bad, throwing up everyday, i was scared of food, i was scared of pretty much everything in my life. i was depressed, i was a child but hell yeah i was so depressed. and now i’m almost 20 and it feels like those days were just yesterday, some days i’m feeling great about my life, some other days i can’t even hear the word cancer or chemo that i will cry my eyes out...
at 12,13,14 i realized how evil people around you can be, people are mean just because. i was bullied when i came back to school and ugh today it still hurts in my heart that people are this cruel... I see the world with completely different eyes now. Our health, in general, is the most important thing in our life. We always must know that.
it’s 2020 and i’m still recovering all the wounds, I know it will take time...
Just to share with you that we’re all on this together, I really hope you’re doing okay. after all life is not fair, but we are. we are good people, we deserve to live a happy life. and remember do not put your health behind anything. 🍀 do not listen to people, they know nothing about our lives, they know nothing about our scars and our past. they know nothing. you look beautiful just the way you are, we are all special in our own ways.
you’re strong girl, keep going x
